        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary><span class="faq-tag tag-green">TRADES</span>Do I need to arrange my own tiler and plumber separately?</summary>
          <div class="faq-body">
            <p>No. This is our most important differentiator. Our own team handles all the plumbing, tiling and fitting. You do not need to arrange, coordinate or manage separate tradesmen. One team, one quote, one point of contact throughout. This is particularly valuable in Liverpool where coordinating multiple trades in terrace properties can be very disruptive.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary><span class="faq-tag tag-orange">SUPPLY</span>Can I supply my own bathroom suite and just pay for labour?</summary>
          <div class="faq-body">
            <p>Yes. If you have already purchased your bathroom suite from a showroom or retailer, we can provide a competitive labour-only quote. We are experienced fitting products from all major brands and retailers including Bathstore, Victorian Plumbing, B&Q, Wickes and specialist Liverpool bathroom showrooms. Please ensure products are complete before the installation date.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary><span class="faq-tag tag-navy">VALUE</span>Will a new bathroom increase my Liverpool property value?</summary>
          <div class="faq-body">
            <p>Yes. A well-fitted new bathroom can increase Liverpool property value by up to 5%. For a property worth £200,000 that is a £10,000 uplift from an investment starting at £4,500. Liverpool estate agents consistently identify bathroom quality as one of the top three factors in buyer decisions. See <a href="https://www.gov.uk/guidance/energy-performance-certificates" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GOV.UK EPC guidance</a> for how bathroom improvements affect property energy ratings.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary><span class="faq-tag tag-green">OLD HOMES</span>Can you fit a new bathroom in Liverpool's Victorian terraces?</summary>
          <div class="faq-body">
            <p>Yes. We specialise in Liverpool's period properties. Victorian terraces present specific challenges: limited pipe access, solid walls, old waste stacks and no cavity. Our engineers have 30 years experience working in these properties and understand how to route new plumbing with minimal disruption to original features. We assess every property individually at the free survey.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary><span class="faq-tag tag-orange">WET ROOM</span>What is the difference between a wet room and a walk-in shower?</summary>
          <div class="faq-body">
            <p>A walk-in shower has a shower tray with a low lip or threshold. A wet room has no tray and uses a fully tanked and waterproofed floor that drains into a floor-level drain. Wet rooms require specialist tanking to prevent water seeping through the floor and into the room below, which is why they cost more. We strongly recommend using experienced wet room specialists rather than a standard bathroom fitter who does not specialise in tanking.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
